to be about whether any extra setup is needed for a library beyond the standard scaffold. Existing tests include the build, but they fail two locator tests that don't involve the servlet.\\n\\nI’m wondering if, to reach meaningful coverage, the servlet API is always necessary. Some classes don’t require it, but since the library's central purpose is building a WebDAV server, servlet classes might be significant after all.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Examining dependencies for compilation**\\n\\nI’m considering whether I can compile by just importing `org.apache.jackrabbit.webdav.DavServletRequest` without including all artifacts. I suspect it might error due to missing `HttpServletRequest`. So, yes, I probably need additional dependencies. \\n\\nMaybe I should add `org.slf4j:slf4j-simple:1.5.3`, but since it’s marked as runtimeOnly in the existing setup, it doesn’t fit the testImplementation scope. Since it’s not essential, I might skip it. I’m also wondering if `org.apache.jackrabbit:jackrabbit-jcr-server` is necessary.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"action\": \"advisory_preparation\",\n  \"summary\": \"Jackrabbit WebDAV is a generic WebDAV client/server utility library, not a standalone server. Its resolved POM marks the Servlet API as provided, while public server/request types extend Servlet classes, so meaningful server-side coverage needs the Servlet API added to the test classpath. No Docker service or environment property is indicated.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"dependency\",\n      \"coordinate\": \"javax.servlet:servlet-api:2.4\",\n      \"scope\": \"testImplementation\",\n      \"reason\": \"The artifact exposes server-side APIs such as AbstractWebdavServlet, DavServletRequest, and WebdavRequestImpl that depend on javax.servlet types, but jackrabbit-webdav declares servlet-api as a provided dependency, so generated tests need it explicitly on the test classpath.\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"No environment variables or system properties are indicated. Prefer in-memory stubs/mocks for DavResource, DavSessionProvider, DavLocatorFactory, servlet requests/responses, and XML/client method objects; do not assume a live Jackrabbit repository or WebDAV server is available.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"The 2.0-beta4 parent POM manages servlet-api as 2.3, while the existing scaffold uses 2.4; 2.4 is compatible with the current tests, but Gradle/native verification remains authoritative.\",\n    \"The reported failure is a native test runtime failure after image build, so setup alone may not address the failing assertions or reachability metadata needs.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_038462f0c4011710016a42a8f1479c81979065a65e1949b902\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 2356, "output": 857, "cacheRead": 34304, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 37517, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782753511336, "responseId": "resp_038462f0c4011710016a42a8e7fc588197a1060f45a991e7eb"}}
